# Tag recommendations for Smart Push Notifications

In this dashboard you can check for your SPNS device secret

* the tags you will be targeted
* the view history of your SPNS device secret that was used by AI for building the recommendations

To run this notebook fill in your SPNS device secret id in the paragraph titled **Enter your SPNS Device Secret ID**.
Then hit the button "Run all paragraphs" and wait until the notebook is done running.
The button "Run all paragraphs" can be found on the top, it's the play button next to this notebook's title **/Rakesh/tags/scores/UserTagCombinedScores**.

import org.apache.spark.sql.Encoders
import org.apache.spark.sql.functions._

case class ScoreOnDisk(srcUniqueId: String, dstUniqueId: String, score: Double, source: String)
val scoreSchema = Encoders.product[ScoreOnDisk].schema

val scoresFolder = "s3://sanoma.dataservices.team/cda/prod/recommendations/scores"
//val scoresFolder = "s3://sanoma-smbene-bigdata-team/dsnl/prod/recommendations/scores"

def readScores(scoreName: String, numReadMinimal: Int) = {
    println(s"reading from $scoresFolder/$scoreName")
    spark
        .read
        .option("header", "true")
        .schema(scoreSchema)
        .csv(s"$scoresFolder/$scoreName")
        .withColumn("numRead", round(exp(col("score") - 1), 2))
        .withColumnRenamed("srcUniqueId", "tag")
        .filter(s"numRead >= $numReadMinimal")
}

paragraphs.text:
%md
## How recommendations are computed

The recommended tags are computed in two ways:

1. *Business rule heavy reader*
you are added when you are in the top 20% of users who reads most about a tag
(displayed in the paragraph with the title **You're a heavy reader for the tags**)
2. *AI*
we check the usage patterns using Machine Learning algorithms
(displayed in the paragraph with the title **AI suggests the following tags**)

In the smart push notification algorithm we combine the *Heavy Reader* and *AI* tags into a single set of tags on which you will be targeted.
These tags are displayed in the paraph wit the title **The tags you will be targeted with**.
